Andrew Mowbray (Co-Director)

Professor of Law and Information Technology, UTS

Email Phone Website

Co-Director since January 1995, Andrew is the principal software author and technical director of AustLII.

He has degrees in Computing Science and Law. He wrote the sino search engine, the hypertext markup software, and the ysh inferencing engine.

Pre-AustLII, Andrew wrote the DataLex Workstation Software, the AIRS free text retrieval engine and the LES legal expert system shell. He teaches and publishes in computerised legal research, computerisation of law and information technology law.

Graham Greenleaf (Co-Director)

Professor of Law and Information Systems, UNSW

Email Phone Website

Co-Director since January 1995, Graham has joint responsibility for the overall development and direction of AustLII and WorldLII.

He has general responsibility for AustLII's funding, obtaining new data sources, and the WorldLII / Project DIAL facilities.

He has degrees in Arts and Law, and is a Fellow of the Australian Computer Society. He has researched and taught in the areas of intellectual property, privacy, cyberspace law and computerisation of law since 1982.

Philip Chung (Executive Director)

Senior Lecturer in Law, UNSW

Email Phone

He is experienced in large scale legal publishing on the Internet, computerised legal research, computer legal applications and automated text processing.
